Dar es Salaam. More than 300 new farmers are this year set to join Serengeti Breweries Limited (SBL) s agri-business project that provides farmers with high quality seedlings free of charge, links them to financial institutions to acquire capital needed for large scale farming and supplies them with fertilizers and other farming implements.According to SBL corporate relations director John Wanyancha, the brewer s project facilitates farmers growing maize, sorghum and millet, enabling the company to increase its locally-sourced raw materials it uses in beer production.SBL has three breweries located in Dar es Salaam, Moshi and Mwanza. To date, this project has benefited more than 100 core farmers across various regions including Arusha, Manyara, Mbeya, Kilimanjaro, Singida, Morogoro, Shinyanga and Dodoma who cultivate a total of 20,000 acres, Mr Wanyancha said.